&gt; Insolation is the amount of solar radiation energy received per unit area on Earth’s surface in a given time.

* It is usually measured in watts per square meter (W/m²) or calories/cm²/min.
* Insolation depends on factors like latitude, season, time of day, and atmospheric conditions.
* Roughly 1 part in 2 billion of the Sun’s total energy output actually falls on Earth.
</md></sn><sn><md>## Heat Budget{.text-center}

The Sun is the primary source of energy for Earth. The total solar energy reaching Earth is called **insolation**. Insolation is not evenly distributed across the globe due to the curvature of the Earth, the tilt of its axis, and the presence of clouds and aerosols.

